    "created_at": "2024-03-08T11:15:33Z",
    "updated_at": "2024-03-08T11:15:33Z",
    "body": "> Just because an executable resides in a venv/bin/ folder and is called python it shouldn't automatically be assumed that it's an actual version of Python\r\n\r\nLike how else would we figure out something is \"an actual version of Python\".\r\n\r\nWhat kind of attack is this defending against?",
