    "updated_at": "2024-03-08T20:57:04Z",
    "body": "No comments on the security implications mention above, but more an additional problem: adding `.venv/bin/python` to the list might end as a surprise for the users in case the venv is not activated: you see the python version for the venv, but when you execute `python3`, you get something else. If the venv is activated, the other (default) entries are taking care of displaying the right thing because the venv is the first entry in $PATH.\r\n\r\nFor that reason, I would also argue in favor of removing that example.",
