    "body": "> My idea is that by activating the venv I'm actively taking a decision about the thing's safety, which I'm not doing by just stepping into the folder.\r\n\r\nAh yeah. I see that starship executes lots of stuff anyway as part of its functioning. That could already be something that not everybody needs to be super enthusiastic about but I agree that executing files that are in well-known system folders is a different matter from just grabbing something from any folder I might be in.",
